name: 3-hydroxy-4-nitrobenzoic acid

The melting point of a compound can be influenced by several factors including molecular weight, symmetry, kinds of functional groups, and intermolecular forces such as hydrogen bonding, dipole-dipole interactions, and Van der Waals forces. - The carboxylic group is already accounted for in the base value of benzoic acid.
Adding these values together gives the predicted melting point.
Prediction: 122 (base value for benzoic acid) + 50 (hydroxyl group) + 40 (nitro group) = 212 degrees Celsius
